C=====True=====76
As a young boy, this noble’s predilection for surrounding himself with peasants led to him
being known as “The Great Fool of Owari.” This man innovated the use of the concentrated
volley to defeat the Takeda Clan at the Battle of Nagashino. The Honno-ji incident led to this
daimyo’s death and the killing of clan leader Akechi Mitsuhide at the hand of this man’s disciple,
Toyotomi Hideyoshi. For the point, name this ally of Tokugawa Ieyasu, known as the “Great
Unifier” of Japan.=====
Oda Nobunaga =====